==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Embale
<hw>Em*bale"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>emballer</ets>; pref. <ets>em-</ets> (L. <ets>in</ets>) +
<ets>balle</ets> bale. See 1st <er>Bale</er>.]</ety> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To make up into a bale or pack.</def>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To bind up; to inclose.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Legs . . . <qex>embaled</qex> in golden buskins.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emball</ent>⟦br⟧
